title: My Old House
author: joe
text: my old house was actually a condo i lived there with my parents and,  eventually,  my sister.  whenever 6 o'clock rolled around,  my mom and i would always go down to the parking lot of the condo complex.  we would wait for my dad to come home;  the highlight of my day that consisted mainly of naps,  eating and playing with blocks.  then we would go back to our condo,  watch jeopardy,  nickelodeon,  and wheel of fortune.  i would play with my dad for a while then go to bed.  a simple lifestyle for a simple life.  all i needed at the time,  all i wanted,  all i knew that existed.

title: Baseball
author: joe
text: baseball more than a way to pass time.  a sport for some,  a life for others.  if you truly love the game,  you'll follow the game,  you'll play it you'll enjoy teaching others,  beginners.  there once was a boy that lived down my street,  whenever i practiced on my tee,  he would come over,  just to watch.  he never asked me anything,  he never said a word.  after a while,  he would leave,  a big smile on his face.  that boy was a true lover of the game.  one day,  i let him take a couple of swings on my tee,  and i handed him my 23 ounce aluminum bat,  thinking he could never hold it.  he grabbed it out of my hands,  ready and willing to hit.  he took a couple of swings,  not having any trouble at all.  when he left,  you should have seen the look on his face.  if that kid ever makes it to the mlb,  he won't play for the money,   to show off,  or anything else.  he would play for the love of the game,  because for him,  baseball was life.

title: My treat
author: keeley
text: as a treat,  i like to eat tasty sour keys my mouth tingles as the sourness swirls through my mouth.  i have trouble staying at ease.  i wiggle and i giggle while the sour taste is tickling my whole mouth.  sour keys come in bright colors orange,  green,  and yellow.  they are squishy like marsh mellow.  sour keys are my favorite candy so you try one and your taste buds will be in for a treat.

title: My Horse, Bella
author: keeley
text: bella neighs loudly when she sees her friends. she gallops around like the strong breeze whipping in the air.  she is a brown and white patched mare.  she looks up upon the fields as she is concentrating hard like a math test you see.  she trots like she is walking on sand made of crystals.  she is so grand.  her ears flick back and forth listening to everything i say and never ever looks away.  what a wonderful horse she is today.

title: Taste buds
